      "content": "Herbal remedies are not exempt from powerful chemical interactions, and St. John's Wort is known to affect how your body processes medications. Even half a dose can trigger dangerous levels of serotonin when combined with sertraline. The worst-case scenario is serotonin syndrome, which can cause rapid heart rate, high blood pressure, and seizures. For immediate focus, try taking a short walk outside to get some natural light and a quick burst of fresh air.",
      "source": "target",
